<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,1390,1519]" box="[160,276,1390,1415]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1390,1415]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" reason="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,1390,1519]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">Green sharpshooters, crown and anterior third of pronotum yellow; aedeagus with two small semi-fused dentiform processes on ventral portion: one subapical and one apical, and pair of wing-shaped processes on dorsoapical portion.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="1530" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,1564,1727]" box="[160,275,1564,1589]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">
<heading box="[160,275,1564,1589]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,275,1564,1589]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" reason="3">Comment</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,1564,1727]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">
The presence of the subapical dentiform process is a homoplastic autapomorphy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Leal &amp; Creão-Duarte &amp; Mejdalani, 2016" authorityName="Leal &amp; Creão-Duarte &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">S. amazonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[311,402,1634,1658]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shared with 
<emphasis box="[556,870,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[556,714,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subolivacea">S. subolivacea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Leal &amp; Creão-Duarte &amp; Mejdalani, 2016" authorityName="Leal &amp; Creão-Duarte &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2016" box="[728,870,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osteiphera" status="sp. nov.">S. osteiphera</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[880,970,1634,1658]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Leal" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[1033,1149,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oglobini">
<emphasis box="[1033,1149,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">S. oglobini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the pair of wing-shaped processes of the aedeagus is a homoplastic autapomorphy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Leal &amp; Creão-Duarte &amp; Mejdalani, 2016" authorityName="Leal &amp; Creão-Duarte &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2016" box="[288,456,1703,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[288,456,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">S. amazonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[465,553,1703,1727]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shared with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Leal 2014)" baseAuthorityName="Leal" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[704,992,1703,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subolivacea">
<emphasis box="[704,858,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529">S. subolivacea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Leal AH" box="[873,983,1703,1727]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1529" refId="ref13044" refString="Leal AH 2014. Revisao taxonomica e analise filogenetica de Scopogonalia Young, 1977 com a descricao de uma especie nova do grupo externo (Insecta: Hemiptera: Cicadellidae) [D. Sc. dissertation]. Joao Pessoa (Brazil): Universidade Federal da Paraiba." type="book" year="2014">Leal 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,725,142,167]" box="[160,725,142,167]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,317,142,167]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="3">Type locality.</emphasis>
Itacoatiara, Amazonas state, 
<collectingCountry box="[658,721,143,167]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,217,242]" box="[160,1156,217,242]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,248,217,242]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="3">Length.</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[325,428,218,242]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<quantity box="[438,524,218,242]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" unit="mm" value="5.7">5.7 mm</quantity>
. Male 
<typeStatus box="[595,708,218,242]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">paratypes</typeStatus>
, 5.0– 
<quantity box="[764,850,218,242]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" unit="mm" value="5.9">5.9 mm</quantity>
; female 
<typeStatus box="[943,1056,218,242]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">paratypes</typeStatus>
, 6.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,292,629]" box="[160,410,292,317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
<heading box="[160,410,292,317]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,410,292,317]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="3">External morphology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,292,629]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[239,353,328,352]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
) moderately produced anteriorly, median length of crown approximately 1/2 interocular width and 1/3 transocular width; anterior margin narrowly rounded in dorsal view; ocelli located behind anterior eye angles, each closer to adjacent anterior eye angle than to median line of crown, situated at pair of slight concavities. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[295,409,467,491]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
) with width approximately equal to transocular width; lateral margins convergent anteriorly; dorsopleural carinae incomplete, not attaining eyes, oblique. Fore wings (
<figureCitation box="[399,508,536,560]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
) opaque, membrane including all of apical cells, extending anteriorly along costal margin as far as basal half of wing. Hind legs with length of first tarsomere greater than combined length of two more distal ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1157,680,808]" box="[160,285,680,705]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
<heading box="[160,285,680,705]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,680,705]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="3">Coloration</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1157,680,808]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
Background colour of crown, anterior third of pronotum, and mesonotum greenish-yellow, remainder of dorsum green (
<figureCitation box="[481,588,750,774]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
). Crown with round green maculae on and around ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[232,338,784,808]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
). Ventral region of body yellow; tergum of abdomen dark brown to black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,859,1230]" box="[160,331,859,884]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
<heading box="[160,331,859,884]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,331,859,884]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="3">Male genitalia</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,859,1230]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[258,362,894,918]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6B</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, moderately produced posteriorly; dorsal margin slightly concave; posterodorsal margin broadly convex; apex acute; process arising from ventral margin and extending posterodorsally as far as apex of pygofer. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[167,273,998,1022]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6C</figureCitation>
) not extending posteriorly as far as apex of pygofer, gradually tapered towards apex; macrosetae uniseriate along outer margins. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[797,906,1033,1057]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6D</figureCitation>
) slender, without preapical lobe, strongly curved. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[631,742,1068,1092]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6D</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1005,1111,1068,1092]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6E</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, directed posterodorsally, with two tiny semi-fused dentiform processes on ventral portion, larger subapical one and smaller apical one, and pair of wing-shaped processes on dorsoapical portion (
<figureCitation box="[547,677,1171,1196]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6E–F</figureCitation>
). Paraphyses (
<figureCitation box="[838,943,1172,1196]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6E</figureCitation>
) paired, extending below aedeagus, with rami curved dorsally, not attaining aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1155,1281,1583]" box="[160,359,1281,1306]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
<heading box="[160,359,1281,1306]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,359,1281,1306]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="3">Female genitalia</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1155,1281,1583]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
Abdominal sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[420,527,1316,1340]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6G</figureCitation>
) longer than wide, lateral margins parallel, tapering near apex; posterior margin with concavity. Valvulae II (
<figureCitation box="[749,861,1351,1375]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[179,1136,138,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-199@7.[178,1138,137,1069]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 6. Scopogonalia amazonensis sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) apex of aedeagus, ventral view; (G) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (H) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.25 mm; F = 0.13 mm; G–H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 6H</figureCitation>
) expanded beyond basal curvature and gradually tapered towards acute apex; dorsal margin approximately rectilinear and parallel to ventral margin; preapical prominence distinct; teeth of basal and median portions inclined trapezoid (
<figureCitation box="[594,722,1455,1479]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1281,1304]" captionTargetBox="[179,1135,143,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-78@12.[178,1138,142,1250]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Scopogonalia osteiphera sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G–J) valvula II of ovipositor: (G) lateral view; (H) tooth at median portion; (I) teeth at apical portion; (J) apex. PT, primary tooth; DT, denticle; DM, dorsal margin and VM, ventral margin of dentate apical area. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–G = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206551/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 11H</figureCitation>
), becoming triangular towards apex (
<figureCitation box="[167,279,1489,1513]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1281,1304]" captionTargetBox="[179,1135,143,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-78@12.[178,1138,142,1250]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Scopogonalia osteiphera sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G–J) valvula II of ovipositor: (G) lateral view; (H) tooth at median portion; (I) teeth at apical portion; (J) apex. PT, primary tooth; DT, denticle; DM, dorsal margin and VM, ventral margin of dentate apical area. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–G = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206551/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 11I</figureCitation>
); first ones with flat posterior area, which becomes gradually smaller towards apex, where it is absent; denticles on all teeth and on apical portion; ventral dentate apical portion greater than dorsal one (
<figureCitation box="[522,635,1559,1583]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1281,1304]" captionTargetBox="[179,1135,143,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-78@12.[178,1138,142,1250]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Scopogonalia osteiphera sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G–J) valvula II of ovipositor: (G) lateral view; (H) tooth at median portion; (I) teeth at apical portion; (J) apex. PT, primary tooth; DT, denticle; DM, dorsal margin and VM, ventral margin of dentate apical area. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–G = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206551/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">Figure 11J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1155,1633,1727]" box="[160,285,1633,1658]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
<heading box="[160,285,1633,1658]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1633,1658]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" reason="3">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1155,1633,1727]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leal &amp; Creão-Duarte &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2016" box="[402,543,1669,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonensis">
<emphasis box="[402,543,1669,1693]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1530">amazonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, refers to the Amazon region, where the specimens were found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
